brewery.brewery_description:
After what seems like an epic and eternal fit-out period, we are truly excited to welcome our community to Mullumbimby's first brewery. We can't wait to show off all the hard work that has taken place. Followed by sharing a few tasty brews with old and new friends in the beer garden whilst watching the sun set behind Mt Chincogan and beyond.

Our small batch brews are crafted here in the majestic Northern Rivers of NSW, Byron Bay's Hinterland. We use only the finest ingredients and our brews are uniquely fermented to the vibrations of music. For happier yeast and beers that sing the soul.

Our brewery is family & dog (on lead) friendly.

beer.beer_description: This soft juicy hazy IPA is inspired by what put Mullumbimby on the map. No, sorry it does not contain nefarious ingredients other than a solid dose of Kiwi Dub throughout fermentation.
An American style Pale Ale boasting tropical and citrus hop aromas, low bitterness and medium bodied finish.
A flavourful Pale Ale brewed with Aussie Vic secret hops. An easy drinking beer to celebrate the special way of life we all love, here and in the hinterland.

A rich, delicious full-bodied white stout infused with PNG organic vanilla beans, freshly roasted coffee beans soaked for a week in fireball whisky and rounded off by organic Peruvian cacao. Seriously complex flavours that will keep you coming back for another sip….!
A full bodied stout with the subtle presence of roasted macadamias and the smokey complexity of Manuka malts.
Carefully crafted to be smooth and malty with a delicious chocolate aroma and a hint of roast. This well-balanced and easy drinking Porter is sure to bring you over to the dark side!
A Chai Spiced Ginger Beer.
Pure and simple, this south pacific take on a classic Pilsner. Boasts a tasty malt base, floral and delicate Kiwi hop character and a clean, crisp finish.
A ridiculously refreshing Raspberry Sour, Berliner Weisse. If you have never tried a sour beer before, this is a great introduction.
GABS2024 Festival Beer - Ingredients; Malt Hops Deep Purple Water Black Berries Yeast A refreshing Blackberry Gose Sour, fermented 24/7 to the sound vibrations of Deep Purple.
An interesting twist on a classic beer style. Pale Lager Infused with Organic Cacao, this gives this once sacred ingredient the perfect canvas to shine.

Harmonics pretty much sums up this easy drinking Lager. Opposing ingredients such as malt sweetness and hop bitterness come together to balance each other out. We thought it only appropriate to play Classical music on endless repeat for this classic beer style.
A refreshing Summer Ale with a light malt body, a crisp, dry finish and balanced hop bitterness.
Make IPA great again…! This old school IPA is packed full of hops. A decent body that is rounded out with a balanced bitterness.
British Bitter
A lush full-bodied stout layered with Organic Peruvian Cacao and freshly roasted Organic Highland PNG coffee beans by Mullum`s own The Branches.
Yeast driven
This new refreshing sour is packed full of Mango & Passionfruit and has been fermented to Brazilian Samba.
Imperial lychee and pineapple sour
A lush tropical coconut IPA. Organic toasted coconut chips, mixed with medium body.
The latest in our Haze Series. This brew is packed with a mountain of the American hops, delivering a lush tropical fruit salad flavour with a smooth, full body.
A big oatmeal stout
Fermented to Caribbean music,
